---
import Page from '../layouts/Page.astro';
---

<Page title="Research" description="Our research themes in computational and statistical genomics">

  <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-6 py-20">

    <!-- Header -->
    <p class="font-mono text-[0.68rem] tracking-[0.18em] uppercase text-teal-600 mb-3">
      What we study
    </p>

    <h1 class="font-serif text-4xl text-stone-900 font-normal mb-4">
      Research
    </h1>

    <div class="w-10 h-0.5 bg-gradient-to-r from-blue-600 to-teal-500 mb-6"></div>

    <p class="text-stone-500 text-lg leading-relaxed max-w-4xl mb-24">
      We focus on two interconnected research areas: developing scalable computational
      methods for genomic data, and applying them to biobanks to understand the genetic
      basis of human disease.
    </p>

    <!-- THEMES -->
    <div class="space-y-28">

      <!-- Theme 01 -->
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-14 items-center">

        <img
          src="/images/lab/theme1.png"
          alt="Structural variation research"
          class="w-full rounded-xl shadow-md border border-stone-100 object-cover"
        />

        <div>
          <p class="font-mono text-[0.62rem] text-stone-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">
            Theme 01
          </p>

          <h2 class="font-serif text-2xl text-stone-900 font-normal mb-3">
            Structural Variation & Disease
          </h2>

          <p class="text-stone-500 leading-relaxed mb-4">
            Large genomic rearrangements — deletions, duplications, inversions —
            are often overlooked in standard GWAS studies, yet account for a
            substantial fraction of heritable disease risk. We develop methods
            to detect, phase, and functionally interpret structural variants
            at biobank scale, integrating them with transcriptomic and
            proteomic data.
          </p>

          <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2">
            {['SV detection','Multi-omics','UK Biobank','FinnGen'].map(t => (
              <span class="font-mono text-[0.62rem] px-2 py-0.5 bg-stone-100 text-stone-500 rounded">
                {t}
              </span>
            ))}
          </div>
        </div>

      </div>


      <!-- Theme 02 -->
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-14 items-center">

        <div class="md:order-2">
          <img
            src="/images/lab/theme2.png"
            alt="Population haplotypes research"
            class="w-full rounded-xl shadow-md border border-stone-100 object-cover"
          />
        </div>

        <div class="md:order-1">
          <p class="font-mono text-[0.62rem] text-stone-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">
            Theme 02
          </p>

          <h2 class="font-serif text-2xl text-stone-900 font-normal mb-3">
            Population Haplotypes & Identity-by-Descent
          </h2>

          <p class="text-stone-500 leading-relaxed mb-4">
            We analyze genetic relationships within and between populations
            by identifying shared haplotype segments — regions inherited from
            a recent common ancestor. This illuminates human population history,
            enables powerful disease mapping through IBD, and underpins accurate
            genotype imputation.
          </p>

          <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2">
            {['Haplotype phasing','IBD','Population genetics','SHAPEIT5'].map(t => (
              <span class="font-mono text-[0.62rem] px-2 py-0.5 bg-stone-100 text-stone-500 rounded">
                {t}
              </span>
            ))}
          </div>
        </div>

      </div>


      <!-- Theme 03 -->
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-14 items-center">

        <img
          src="/images/lab/theme3.png"
          alt="Low coverage sequencing research"
          class="w-full rounded-xl shadow-md border border-stone-100 object-cover"
        />

        <div>
          <p class="font-mono text-[0.62rem] text-stone-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">
            Theme 03
          </p>

          <h2 class="font-serif text-2xl text-stone-900 font-normal mb-3">
            Low-Coverage Sequencing & Imputation
          </h2>

          <p class="text-stone-500 leading-relaxed mb-4">
            SNP arrays have dominated human genetics for two decades,
            but low-coverage whole-genome sequencing is rapidly becoming
            a cost-effective alternative. We develop statistical methods
            such as GLIMPSE that recover accurate genotypes — including
            rare variants — from sequencing depths as low as 0.1×.
          </p>

          <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2">
            {['lcWGS','GLIMPSE2','Rare variants','Ancient DNA'].map(t => (
              <span class="font-mono text-[0.62rem] px-2 py-0.5 bg-stone-100 text-stone-500 rounded">
                {t}
              </span>
            ))}
          </div>
        </div>

      </div>


      <!-- Theme 04 -->
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-14 items-center">

        <div class="md:order-2">
          <img
            src="/images/lab/theme4.png"
            alt="Computational genomics algorithms"
            class="w-full rounded-xl shadow-md border border-stone-100 object-cover"
          />
        </div>

        <div class="md:order-1">
          <p class="font-mono text-[0.62rem] text-stone-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">
            Theme 04
          </p>

          <h2 class="font-serif text-2xl text-stone-900 font-normal mb-3">
            Scalable Computational Algorithms
          </h2>

          <p class="text-stone-500 leading-relaxed mb-4">
            All our biological questions are ultimately constrained by
            computation. We design algorithms that scale to millions of
            genomes. Core methodological themes include Hidden Markov
            models on haplotype space, Positional Burrows-Wheeler Transform
            (PBWT), extensions of the Li–Stephens model, and compressed
            reference panel representations.
          </p>

          <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2">
            {['HMM','PBWT','Li-Stephens','IMPUTE5'].map(t => (
              <span class="font-mono text-[0.62rem] px-2 py-0.5 bg-stone-100 text-stone-500 rounded">
                {t}
              </span>
            ))}
          </div>
        </div>

      </div>

    </div>

  </div>

</Page>
